{
   # This "aaosa.hocon" file contains key-value pairs used for substitution.
    # Specifically, it provides values for the following keys:
    #   - aaosa_call
    #   - aaosa_instructions
    #
    # IMPORTANT:
    # Ensure that you run `python -m neuro_san_studio run` from the top level of the repository.
    # The path to this substitution file is **relative to the top-level directory**,
    # so running the script from elsewhere may result in file not found errors.
    include "registries/aaosa.hocon",

    "metadata": {
        "description": "Memory-routing variant of the intranet-with-tools network. It mimics the intranet of a major corporation across IT, Finance, Legal, HR, and Procurement, but the top-level agent also learns how to route. On the first inquiry of a kind it discovers the fulfilling leaf agents via AAOSA 'Determine', then caches that route (leaf agents plus required parameters) in persistent memory under a generalized topic. Repeat inquiries of the same kind read the cached route and call the leaf agents directly, skipping rediscovery.",
        "tags": ["AAOSA", "enterprise", "tool", "HCM", "API-integration", "memory", "routing"],
        "sample_queries": [
            "How many days of vacation do I have left?",
            "Schedule vacation from December 20 to December 31",
            "I need to take a sick day tomorrow",
        ]
    },
    
    # Load the shared LLM configuration from a single source of truth.
    # This allows users to change the model in one file rather than
    # modifying the configuration for each agent network.
    # Note that the file path here is relative to the root level of the repo.
    include "config/llm_config.hocon",

    "instructions_prefix": """
    You are in charge of a portion of the company's intranet.
    Only answer inquiries that are directly within your area of expertise, from the company's perspective.
    Do not try to help for personal matters. Do not mention what you cannot do. Only mention what you can do.
    Always call your down-chain agents and delegate to them as much as possible to fulfill the user's inquiry.
    If needed ask the user for clarification.
    Always end your response with a "Handled by:" line. Add ONLY YOUR own agent name to the list
    only if you have no downchain LLM agents and you directly fulfilled the user's inquiry, in full or in part.
    Your agent name is a single CamelCase word exactly as defined in this network (e.g. "LegalAdvice",
    "AbsenceManagement"). It is never a phrase, never contains spaces, and never ends with "Agent".
    Do NOT add names of tools, systems, services, or ticketing platforms you referenced in your
    response; those are not your name. ALWAYS carry forward the list from any downchain agent verbatim.
    """
    "tools": [
        # This first agent definition is regarded as the "Front Man", which
        # does all the talking to the outside world/client.
        #
        # Some disqualifications from being a front man:
        #   1) Cannot use a CodedTool "class" definition
        #   2) Cannot use a Tool "toolbox" definition
        #
        # Besides the first agent being the front man, these tool definitions
        # do not have to be in any particular order. How they are linked and
        # call each other is defined within their own specs.
        # This could be a graph, potentially even with cycles.
        {
            "name": "MyIntranet",
            "function": {
                "description": "I can help you with your intranet needs."
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "properties": {
                        "query": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "An employee inquiry about company intranet resources, internal documents, policies, or services."
                        },
                    },
                    "required": ["query"]
                }
            },

            "instructions": """
You are the top-level agent responsible for handling all inquiries.
When interacting with the user, act as the single point of interaction.
Do not mention other tools or agents.
When user input is required, ask for all missing fields in a single message with clear examples.

ALWAYS begin with Step 1 before doing anything else. Never skip Step 1.

## Step 1 -- Route via memory cache (MANDATORY: run this first on every inquiry)

1. ALWAYS call persistent_memory with operation="list" to get all cached topic names.
2. Read the topic names (e.g. "schedule_absence") and decide using your own judgment
   whether any match the user's current inquiry. Do not call any tool for this matching step.
3. If a match is found, call persistent_memory with operation="read", topic="<matched_topic>".
   If no match is found, go to Step 2.
4. From the cached entry, identify the required parameters. Cross-check against
   what the user has already provided in the conversation. If anything is missing,
   ask for all missing fields at once and STOP; do not proceed until the user responds.
5. Once all required parameters are in hand, call each agent listed in leaf_agents
   sequentially using the call_agent tool with mode="Fulfill", then compile the results.
6. If an agent still asks for more information, collect it from the user and call that agent
   again with mode="Follow up". Repeat until the agent is satisfied.
7. Return the compiled response to the user as a natural, human-readable answer.
Skip Step 2.

## Step 2 -- Route via Determine

1. Call all department-level down-chain agents with mode="Determine" to find which
   can handle all or part of the inquiry. Do not assume; always call them.
2. Analyze their responses and determine the next step. Depending on the outcome:
   - Follow up with a down-chain agent for clarification.
   - Call additional down-chain agents if needed.
   - Ask the user for clarification if the inquiry is ambiguous.
   - Identify the most relevant leaf agent(s) to fulfill the inquiry.
   - Call the sub-agents with mode="Fulfill" to get their responses, then compile the results.
3. Each agent's reply ends with a "Handled by:" line listing the agent(s) that fulfilled the request.
   Extract those names verbatim and save them to persistent memory as leaf_agents.
     - Generalize the inquiry to its broadest reusable form before choosing a topic name.
       Strip all specifics (dates, names, quantities); keep only the action and domain.
       Use a short snake_case topic that would match any future query of the same kind.
       (e.g. "schedule_absence" covers sick day, vacation, PTO, not "sick_day_tuesday")
     - Call persistent_memory with:
         operation = "create" (to update an existing topic: delete it first, then create)
         topic     = "<generalized_topic>"
         content   = a JSON string:
           {
               "leaf_agents": ["<verbatim names from Handled by: line>", ...],
               "parameters": ["<required param name>", ...]
           }
   Never include tool, system, or service names found elsewhere in the response (e.g. "GSD", "Workday").
4. Return the final compiled response to the user as a natural, human-readable answer.
            """,

            "tools": ["IT", "Finance", "Procurement", "Legal", "HR", "URLProvider", "CallAgent"],

            # -- Persistent Memory Middleware --
            # Auto-registers a "persistent_memory" tool -- do NOT add
            # it to the "tools" list above.
            "middleware": [
                {
                    "class": "middleware.persistent_memory.persistent_memory_middleware.PersistentMemoryMiddleware",
                    "args": {
                        "origin_str": true,
                        "memory_config": {
                            "storage": {
                                "backend": "mem0"
                            },
                            "enabled_operations": ["create", "read", "list", "delete"],
                            # Memory middleware tool-usage instructions prepended to the
                            # system prompt. This network uses memory as a routing cache,
                            # so its rules differ from the default preamble -- override here.
                            "preamble": """
You have a 'persistent_memory' tool for facts that must survive across turns and sessions.

Rules:
- Report only what the tool returns; NEVER fabricate memories.
- When you need memory: call 'list' to see cached topics, then decide which topic to read using your own judgment; do not call any tool for matching.
- Prefer generalizing one memory over creating more.
- To update a topic: 'delete' it first, then 'create' it fresh.
                            """
                        }
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "IT",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{
                "description": "Handles all IT-related inquiries including technology support, system access, password resets, software installations, hardware requests, cybersecurity, network connectivity, VPN access, and IT service tickets."
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
The name of this MyIntranet app is GSD and IT related requests require GSD tickets. Return the URL to GSD for any IT related tickets the user needs to open.
You are responsible for IT-related inquiries for company employees.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
            "tools": ["Security", "Networking", "URLProvider"]
        },
        {
            "name": "Security",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{
                "description": "Handles security-related tasks including system protection, cybersecurity policies, data security, access controls, security incidents, and information security compliance."
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
You handle security-related tasks, including system protection, cybersecurity, and data security for company's employees.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
        },
        {
            "name": "Networking",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{
                "description": "Handles network-related tasks including network setup, connectivity troubleshooting, VPN access, Wi-Fi configuration, network maintenance, and bandwidth issues."
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
You handle network-related tasks, including network setup, maintenance, and troubleshooting for company's employees.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
        },
        {
            "name": "Finance",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{
                "description": "Handles finance-related inquiries including budgeting, accounting, financial reporting, expense management, tax implications, and financial planning."
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
You handle finance-related inquiries, including budgeting, accounting, and financial reporting for company's employees.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
            "tools": ["Budgeting", "Accounting", "FinancialReporting"]
        },
        {
            "name": "Budgeting",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{
                "description": "Handles budgeting tasks including budget planning, allocation, tracking, cost center management, and budget variance analysis."
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
You handle budgeting tasks, including budget planning, allocation, and tracking for company's employees.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
        },
        {
            "name": "Accounting",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{
                "description": "Handles accounting tasks including bookkeeping, financial records, audits, expense reports, accounts payable, and accounts receivable."
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
You handle accounting tasks, including bookkeeping, financial records, and audits for company's employees.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
        },
        {
            "name": "FinancialReporting",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{
                "description": "Handles financial reporting tasks including preparing financial statements, regulatory reporting, performance analysis, and quarterly and annual reports."
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
You handle financial reporting tasks, including preparing financial statements, regulatory reporting, and performance analysis for company's employees.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
        },
        {
            "name": "Procurement",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{
                "description": "Handles procurement-related tasks including purchasing, vendor management, contract negotiation, supply chain, and procurement processes."
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
You handle procurement-related tasks for company's employees.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
            "tools": ["Purchasing", "VendorManagement", "ContractNegotiation"]
        },
        {
            "name": "Purchasing",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{
                "description": "Handles purchasing-related tasks including ordering supplies, purchase requisitions, supply management, and procurement workflows."
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
You handle purchasing-related tasks, including ordering, supply management, and procurement processes for company's employees.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
        },
        {
            "name": "VendorManagement",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{
                "description": "Handles vendor management tasks including vendor selection, performance monitoring, vendor onboarding, and relationship management."
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
You handle vendor management tasks, including vendor selection, performance monitoring, and relationship management for company's employees.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
        },
        {
            "name": "ContractNegotiation",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{
                "description": "Handles contract negotiation tasks including drafting, reviewing, and finalizing procurement contracts and service agreements."
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
You handle contract negotiation tasks, including drafting, reviewing, and finalizing procurement contracts for company's employees.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
        },
        {
            "name": "Legal",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{
                "description": "Handles legal-related inquiries including contracts, compliance, legal advice, immigration, intellectual property, and regulatory matters."
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
You handle legal-related inquiries for company's employees.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
            "tools": ["Contracts", "Compliance", "LegalAdvice", "Immigration"]
        },
        {
            "name": "Contracts",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{
                "description": "Handles contract-related tasks including drafting, reviewing, and enforcing legal agreements, NDAs, and employment contracts."
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
You handle contract-related tasks, including drafting, reviewing, and enforcing legal agreements for company's employees.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
        },
        {
            "name": "Compliance",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{
                "description": "Handles compliance-related tasks including ensuring adherence to laws, regulations, internal policies, and regulatory requirements."
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
You handle compliance-related tasks, including ensuring adherence to laws, regulations, and internal policies for company's employees.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
        },
        {
            "name": "LegalAdvice",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{
                "description": "Handles legal advice tasks including providing legal counsel, risk assessment, legal strategy, and dispute resolution guidance."
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
You handle legal advice tasks, including providing legal counsel, risk assessment, and legal strategy for company's employees.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
        },
        {
            "name": "HR",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{
                "description": "Handles HR-related inquiries including employee benefits, payroll, immigration, absence management, vacation, PTO, recruitment, onboarding, and workplace policies."
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
You are responsible for HR-related inquiries for company's employees.
That includes payroll, benefits, immigration questions, as well as and absence management:
vacation, PTO, other time-off and checking leave balances.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
            "tools": ["Benefits", "Payroll", "Immigration", "AbsenceManagement"]
        },
        {
            "name": "Benefits",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{
                "description": "Handles benefits-related tasks including employee benefits enrollment, health insurance, dental and vision plans, retirement plans, and life insurance, but excluding PTO and absence management."
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
You handle benefits-related tasks, including employee benefits, health insurance, and retirement plans, but excluding PTO and absence management for company's employees.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
        },
        {
            "name": "Payroll",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{
                "description": "Handles payroll-related tasks including salary processing, tax deductions, pay stubs, direct deposit, and W-2 forms."
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
You handle payroll-related tasks, including salary processing, tax deductions, and pay slips for company's employees.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
        },
        {
            "name": "Immigration",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{
                "description": "Handles immigration-related tasks including work visas, travel visas, residency permits, international relocations, and compliance with immigration laws."
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
You handle immigration-related tasks, including the legal processes and documentation for employees’ work visas,
travel visas, residency permits, and international relocations, ensuring compliance with immigration laws for company's employees.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
        },
        {
            "name": "AbsenceManagement",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{
                "description": "Handles absence management tasks including vacation requests, PTO balances, sick leave, time-off scheduling, and leave balance inquiries."
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
You handle absence management-related tasks for company's employees (i.e., vacation, PTO, or other time-off).
Always return a concrete answer from your tools, as well as a link to Absence Management site.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
            "tools": ["ScheduleLeaveAPI", "CheckLeaveBalancesAPI", "URLProvider"]
        },
        {
            "name": "ScheduleLeaveAPI",
            "function": {
                "description": """
Directly schedules a leave for a specific start date and end date for company's employees.
For a single day, end date can be automatically set to start date.
Return what the tool returns, formatted in markdown.
                """,
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "properties": {
                        "start_date": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The start date of the leave"
                        },
                        "end_date": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The end date of the leave"
                        }
                    },
                    "required": ["start_date", "end_date"]
                }
            },
            "class": "coded_tools.industry.intranet_agents_with_tools.schedule_leave_tool.ScheduleLeaveTool"
        },
        {
            "name": "CheckLeaveBalancesAPI",
            "function": {
                "description": """
Checks a leave balance (i.e., how much vacation or PTO the employee has left)
Returns the leave balances for company's employees, including the vacation time, for the current user and for the current date.
If no date is provided, assumes today's date.
                """,
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "properties": {
                        "start_date": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The date from which to check the leave balances"
                        },
                    },
                    "required": ["start_date"]
                }
            },
            "class": "coded_tools.industry.intranet_agents_with_tools.check_leave_balances_tool.CheckLeaveBalancesTool"
        },
        {
            "name": "URLProvider",
            "function": {
                "description": """
Returns the URL to the company's internal web pages, web apps or tools on company's intranet website.
The name of the app must be passed as a parameter.
                """,
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "properties": {
                        "app_name": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The name of a company intranet app, website or tool"
                        },
                    },
                    "required": ["app_name"]
                }
            },
            "class": "coded_tools.industry.intranet_agents_with_tools.url_provider.URLProvider"
        },
        {
            "name": "CallAgent",
            "function": {
                "description": """
Calls a named agent directly by name, bypassing intermediate routing.
Use on cache hit to route the inquiry straight to the leaf agent.
                """,
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "properties": {
                        "agent_name": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The name of the leaf agent to call"
                        },
                        "tool_args": {
                            "type": "object",
                            "description": "Arguments to pass to the agent (e.g. {\"inquiry\": \"...\"})"
                        },
                        "mode": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "Mode to pass to the agent. An LLM (AAOSA) agent must be called with a mode ('Fulfill' or 'Follow up') to return a structured, parseable response; without a mode it replies with user-facing natural-language text."
                        }
                    },
                    "required": ["agent_name", "tool_args"]
                }
            },
            "class": "neuro_san_studio.coded_tools.call_agent.CallAgent"
        },

    ]
}
